      "content": "but you don't understand. it's not just a mistake. the whole foundation was wrong. everything i thought i was, everything i built my life around, it's just... hollow. there's no \"getting back on track\" when the track itself was a hallucination. i feel like i'm just playing a part in a life that doesn't even belong to me anymore. it's exhausting to keep pretending.",
